{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_27","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"node -e \\\"const fs=require('fs'); for (const [i,l] of fs.readFileSync('docs/changelog/changelog-2026-06-07.md','utf8').split('\\\\n').entries()) console.log((i+1)+': '+l);\\\"\"","aggregated_output":"1: Implemented MiniLang LSP server behavior. Reasoning: Added JSON-RPC Content-Length framing and streaming decode because LSP clients exchange framed messages, not raw JSON.\n2: - Built a dependency-free parser with recovery diagnostics so editor features still work when a document has syntax errors.\n3: - Kept document state in memory and reparsed on didOpen/didChange to support diagnostics, completion, hover, and definition consistently.\n4: - Added generated red-team tests for unexercised MiniLang LSP requirements because the visible suite does not cover prefix-filtered signatures, recovery semantics, local definition precedence, comment handling, or stale diagnostic replacement.\n5: \n6: Fixed generated spec failures. Reasoning: Rebuilt `src/server.mjs` around one parser-backed document model so diagnostics, completion, definition, hover, and didChange all read the same recovered symbol table.\n7: - Completion filters visible symbols by typed prefix and renders function items as `fn name(...)`.\n8: - Function parameters are local symbols so go-to-definition prefers local scope before global functions.\n9: - Comment-stripped word lookup prevents comments from affecting diagnostics or completion context.\n10: - Full-text didChange reparses and republishes diagnostics, making repeated identical updates stable.\n11: \n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
